TBX C++ library version 0.7.6 has now been released.

The main features of this release are:
 * Removed Alpha from version as it has been used in distributed programs for over 10 years.
 * Support for the RISC OS global clipboard.
 * Added support for TreeView Gadget
 * Added support for Tabs Gadget
 * Added Window key and mouse listeners to listen for events on a Window and it's components
 * Added Caret class to set and read wimp caret position
 * Added show_centred & show_at_pointer when showing an object
 * Added Window focus method to set the focus to an invisible caret in the window.
 * Added key_pressed function to check for current key presses
 * Added intersect & infate methods to the BBox class.
 * Added clip methods for setting/getting graphics clipping area in the OSGraphics class.
 * Added MemoryLoader class as a userful helper base class to create a Loader.
 * SpriteArea clear method and improvements to sizing of sprite area.
 * Fixed bugs in subwindow alignment flags and montonic time comparison functions.
 * Fixed packaging after last release include intermediate built files

TBX is a C++ library to help with the development of
C++ applications for the RISC OS desktop.

It comes with a userguide and reference documentation.

TBX is released under the permissive X11 licence so can be used
with commercial and non-commercial applications without charge.

Addition downloads provide some examples and a
program to help generate simple C++ skeleton projects.

All these packages can be easily downloaded using a
RISC OS Packaging Project manager e.g. !PackMan.

For more information and instruction on how to download
them manually see:

https://sites.google.com/site/alansriscosstuff/tbx
